spanGrp.span: ‘A cat was looking at a bird at the distance with something,
Michi të dú yuli sũẽ-gẽ komĩ' jele wa
something to look from far away.
There the little bird also saw him;
Jeska dú yuli të í sũẽ-gẽ ĩã
thus he/the cat wanted to devour it.
jera jie/ michi je nã jie kata-gle-wã í rö
The little bird looked at him, but not much.
Dú yuli të sũẽ-gẽ dú yuli ka të í sũẽ tã'i
Then the cat comes down and approaches the bird.
Jeska ra michi jẽk jawã-gẽ të jẽk kögewãu mãĩ dú yuli kel ska
The cat… the cat goes up uh…where the water flows down [the drain].
Michi michi mĩ-gẽ-gãu ele jirö diglö kenã-glö
The old lady realized that he wanted to devour the little bird.
Pemamita të í sũẽ-gẽ-nã dú yuli kete-gẽ-wã-ite kueinga
But the little bird manages to escape.
Dú yuli kögẽu í jula nã
The old lady goes out and hits hit with something to protect oneself from the rain [umbrella].
pemamita dögesãu-te í kbe-gẽ jẽk kitiö-glo klĩ yiga wa
Then the old lady brings it down;
the cat keeps figuring out how to devour the bird.
begetese-gẽ-ite begetese-gẽ-ite mẽnẽbi dú yuli kete-gẽ-wã-ite
There go/uh… the little bird locks him up with a toy,
Jeska ra mĩ/ ee dú yuli të jina-glö wa í kötie-gẽ-wã í yiga
but it went into the cat’s snout;
í kögẽu plaja í ku jãrga
í kögẽu í kögẽu kwãwã Jebi
